(4) Parkinsonism: carbidopa-levodopa cautious (may worsen psychosis); lower dose than PD;

(5) Non-pharmacologic for behaviors: structured environment, address triggers;

(6) Autonomic dysfunction: orthostasis (compression stockings, fluid, salt, midodrine, droxidopa), constipation, urinary;

(7) Caregiver education + support — DLB different from AD;

(8) Distinguish:
  • Parkinson's disease dementia (PDD — same pathology, dementia > 1 yr after motor sx; DLB — cognitive onset before or within 1 yr of motor);
  • Alzheimer's (less hallucinations, less parkinsonism, less fluctuation);
  • Vascular dementia;
  • FTD;

