  • Motor control;
  • D2 blockade → EPS (acute dystonia, akathisia, parkinsonism, tardive dyskinesia);
  • Parkinson's disease — neurodegeneration → motor sx;
  • Typical antipsychotics > atypical for EPS risk;

(4) Tuberoinfundibular (hypothalamus → pituitary):
  • Tonic dopamine inhibits prolactin release;
  • D2 blockade → hyperprolactinemia (amenorrhea, galactorrhea, sexual dysfunction, gynecomastia, bone loss);
  • Risperidone, paliperidone, haloperidol highest prolactin elevation;
  • Aripiprazole partial agonist often LOWERS prolactin;

